# scripts/install.ps1 contains Traditional Chinese comments/strings and MUST keep a
# UTF-8 BOM: Windows PowerShell 5.1 (powershell.exe) otherwise reads the .ps1 with
# the system ANSI code page (CP950/Big5 on zh-TW), misparses the Chinese, and fails.
# The BOM (EF BB BF) is committed as the file's leading bytes; Git preserves it as-is.
# Keep these files CRLF and never strip the leading BOM when editing.
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
